# Core Testing Philosophy

## 1. Testing Principle
All tests must validate behavior, not implementation.

Tests define system behavior, not internal structure.

---

## 2. Test Structure (AAA)
All tests must follow:

- Arrange: setup state
- Act: execute behavior
- Assert: verify result

---

## 3. Test Isolation Rule
- Each test must be independent
- No shared mutable state
- Tests must be order-independent

---

## 4. Unit vs Integration Tests

### Unit Tests
- Test logic in isolation
- External dependencies must be mocked or stubbed

### Integration Tests
- Test interaction between components or layers
- May use in-memory or test implementations
- Must not use external production systems

---

## 5. Behavior-Driven Testing (BDD)
- Each test must represent a single behavior
- Use Given / When / Then to describe scenarios when needed
- Do not combine multiple behaviors in one test

---

## 6. Refactor Safety Rule
- Refactoring must not change behavior
- Tests must not be modified unless behavior changes